
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-fan-idr-ipv6-bgp-id-00.txt'>
    <title>"IPv6 BGP Identifier Capability for BGP-4", Peng Fan, Zhenqiang Li</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-fan-idr-ipv6-bgp-id-00.txt</link>
    <description>To solve the problem of BGP Identifier in an IPv6-only network without special configuration and planning considerations, this document extends BGP to allow a BGP Identifier to be a valid IPv6 global unicast address assigned to the BGP speaker.  Protocol extension includes the definition of a BGP capability code, "IPv6 BGP Identifier capability", to be used by a BGP speaker to indicate its support for IPv6 address as a BGP Identifier.  This document updates RFC 4271.</description>
    <dc:date>2014-02-12T08:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
